The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for detecting attacks in Software Defined Networks (SDNs), which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning algorithms (cs.LG) for detecting malicious traffic. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a more robust framework, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
